
                                            On Thursday Simphiwe Makhele was shot at the mine's Welkom offices.
                                         JOHANNESBURG - Harmony Gold management says it’s ready to cooperate with authorities in the search for those behind the murder of one of its senior managers. On Thursday, Simphiwe Makhele was shot in the head at the mine's Welkom offices in the Free State. He died on the scene. Harmony Gold's Marian van der Walt said: “Our security team together with the SAPS will assist in the search for the perpetrators of this act of violence and utter lawlessness.”